Almost 400 people have been arrested since Thursday around Durban. Police Minister, Bheki Cele, joined a festive season safety operation in the city. The operations aim to ensure people are safe this holidays. eNCA’s Thuba Vilane filed this report. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - More than 300 people have been arrested since Thursday around Durban. Police Minister, Bheki Cele, joined a festive season safety operation in the city. READ: Police arrest more than 20,000 online fraudsters worldwide The operations aim to ensure people are safe during the holiday season. Cele says operations like these will be taking place around the country over the festive season. Watch the video above for more details on this story.